This paper deals with decision procedures for the multi-agent epistemic logic, which falls under the category of logic and computation (cs.LO). The paper also involves concepts related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and multi-agent systems (cs.MA). The use of tableau-building procedures is a common technique in logic and automated reasoning, which is covered under the category of logic in computer science (cs.LG). Finally, the paper deals with knowledge representation and reasoning, which is a subfield of computational complexity (cs.CC).
